#Load the ggplot2 library
library(ggplot2)
#read in data
gc_26_scaffolds <- read.csv(file="~/Documents/AMNH_Research/virushunters/gc_output_b_a_nr.csv",
                            header=F,
                            sep=",")
#inspect your new data frame
gc_26_scaffolds
ggplot(data=gc_26_scaffolds, aes(gc_26_scaffolds[,2]))+
  geom_histogram(breaks=seq(26,58,by=1),
                 col="blue",
                 fill="lightblue",
                 alpha= 0.5)

#load in data for cymbomonas genome as a whole
cymbo_gc <- read.csv(file="~/Documents/AMNH_Research/virushunters/cymbo_gc_output.csv",
                     header=F,
                     sep=",")
cymbo_gc
ggplot(data=cymbo_gc, aes(cymbo_gc$V4)) + 
  geom_histogram(breaks=seq(10,90,by=1),
                 col="green",
                 fill="lightgreen",
                 alpha=0.5)

#
ggplot() +
geom_boxplot(data=cymbo_gc,
               aes(x="Cymbomonas",y=cymbo_gc$V4),
               fill="blue",
               alpha=0.5) +
    geom_boxplot(data=gc_26_scaffolds, 
                 aes(x="26 Scaffolds",y=gc_26_scaffolds$V2),
                 fill="green",
                 alpha=0.5)
